post_text: Check this out Dragons!!
shared_text:
Livingston County Library
June 16 at 6:00 PM ¬∑

Do you have a tween or teen (ages 12-18) who loves to read? Our teen Summer Reading Program is underway, and we have some exciting incentives to offer our avid young readers! Bingo cards are available in the Children's Department, and readers can sign up by calling/visiting the library or downloading the Reader Zone app. This year, we are giving away a pair of Skullcandy bluetooth headphones ($80 value), a JBL bluetooth speaker ($35 value), an Amazon gift card ($50 value), a Dominos gift card ($20 value), a Sonic gift card ($10 value), 4 popular books including the latest installment to the Hunger Games series, and snacks! Logging weekly reads and completely bingo cards gain entry into the drawing for the prizes pictured. Help us encourage your teens to read this summer!

Attention FFA members!! Here is an opportunity for you to attend a seminar from State FFA Convention! Turn in proof of participation for EXTRA CREDIT!

National FFA Secretary Kourtney Lehman wanted to offer a workshop to MO FFA members ‚Äì below is her description along with the date and time. If she has more sign up than she can handle at one event I believe the plan is to offer a second time. If you all can share this opportunity through your channels it would be appreciated.

"To Do vs To Be"

"Living in a historical time when the world is facing a pandemic can be extremely stressful. However, even in the most chaotic, confusing situations there is only so much we can control. Throughout the course of this workshop, we will learn how to navigate through this experience by controlling the controllable.

Thursday (4/23) at 4 pm Central Time.

Supplies Needed: 3 pieces of paper, pen/pencil"

Link to sign up is here. Our number is MO0217
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdeYqhAFezsruVNYtEdHfhfjQAObveD8TTz5Rpj8K2gVwqBig/viewform
